00:48.715 --> 00:52.219
Pick up. Pick up, pick up,
pick up, pick up, pick up!

00:52.302 --> 00:54.521
(PANTING)

01:01.812 --> 01:03.564
Sarah! Sarah!

01:03.647 --> 01:05.820
Duncan, what happened to you?

01:05.899 --> 01:08.027
Good. You're okay.
Go down to the basement.

01:08.110 --> 01:09.362
Right now.
(PANTING)

01:11.655 --> 01:13.032
Oh, my God!
What is that?

01:13.115 --> 01:14.788
Do it now! Hurry!

01:19.580 --> 01:20.581
Goddamn it!

01:25.627 --> 01:27.721
(SCREAMING)

02:38.825 --> 02:41.829
(GROWLING)

03:00.639 --> 03:02.983
DOCTOR: And there she blows.

03:03.058 --> 03:05.652
Mr. and Mrs. Hayslip,
take a look.

03:09.022 --> 03:10.194
What is it?

03:11.024 --> 03:13.573
It's definitely something
the doctor should look at.

03:14.444 --> 03:17.243
- He'll be with you in a moment.
- Thank you.

03:17.322 --> 03:19.040
Thanks.

03:25.497 --> 03:27.170
Uh-huh-huh-huh-huh.

03:27.249 --> 03:29.001
Familial adenomatous polypsis.

03:30.544 --> 03:31.716
It's a polyp.

03:32.379 --> 03:34.848
Oh, it sounds really bad.
That sounds bad.

03:35.716 --> 03:37.013
You got a thing in your butt.

03:37.092 --> 03:38.435
- Okay.
- Yeah.

03:38.510 --> 03:40.228
You got a little trooper
in your pooper.

03:40.303 --> 03:42.726
- You don't need him there.
- Is it serious?

03:42.806 --> 03:45.400
It's... it's not that bad.
It's not that serious.

03:45.475 --> 03:47.648
This though,
this is a weird shape.

03:48.103 --> 03:50.697
This is concerning me a little,
but not overly.

03:50.772 --> 03:54.868
Look, in the end,
this lump in your colon

03:54.943 --> 03:58.948
is most likely due to PSM
which is poor stress management.

03:59.364 --> 04:01.241
Look, how long have you had
stomach issues?

04:01.324 --> 04:04.498
- Um, for... ever.
- Mmmmm.

04:04.578 --> 04:05.830
Yeah, he's in the bathroom a lot.

04:05.912 --> 04:08.665
Not, I mean not, not a lot.
I'm in the bathroom

04:08.749 --> 04:11.218
a decent amount of time,
but not like, it's not extreme.

04:11.293 --> 04:13.341
- How often is a lot?
- Hour, hour and a half.

04:13.420 --> 04:15.172
Yeah, about 90 minutes.

04:15.255 --> 04:19.305
That's not, that's...
hugely concerning.

04:19.384 --> 04:21.432
Over the course of
the day, not...

04:21.511 --> 04:23.764
Okay, good thing is,
we can do something about this.

04:23.847 --> 04:25.815
It's an endoscopic polypectomy.

04:25.891 --> 04:29.691
Basically, we insert a camera,
into the anus.

04:29.770 --> 04:30.817
- Okay
- Right?

04:30.896 --> 04:33.570
There's an electrified
wire loop at the end of it,

04:33.648 --> 04:35.116
and we...
(MAKES POPPING NOISE)

04:35.192 --> 04:37.570
...pop it off,
like a plum off a tree.

04:38.236 --> 04:40.989
Being pulled
by an electrified wire loop.

04:41.072 --> 04:43.166
Okay. Okay, I get it.
You don't have to...

04:43.241 --> 04:44.993
You don't have to
describe it anymore.

04:45.076 --> 04:47.875
Do you have a family history
of G.I. problems?

04:47.954 --> 04:50.127
Uh, well, you know, my mom
would gladly tell you

04:50.207 --> 04:53.006
that she's, um, you know, regular
like clockwork. (PANTING)

04:53.084 --> 04:55.257
One of those.
What about your father?

04:55.337 --> 04:57.305
Uh, well, we don't speak.

04:57.380 --> 04:59.974
I haven't spoken to him
in sometime. So...

05:00.050 --> 05:02.644
Look, I think what you're going
to need is some coping mechanisms,

05:02.719 --> 05:05.097
so I can give you the name
of some professionals

05:05.180 --> 05:08.229
- that can help you out.
- Are you talking about a therapist?

05:08.308 --> 05:10.060
Oh, I'm nut...
I'm not a therapy guy.

05:10.143 --> 05:11.770
We can get there.
We'll do it. We'll call him.

05:11.853 --> 05:13.730
Great. Stop by the desk
on your way out.

05:13.814 --> 05:15.862
Talk to Nancy about
scheduling a follow-up.

05:15.941 --> 05:19.070
Until then, you take it down.

05:19.152 --> 05:21.826
- No stress. Keep it quiet.
- Right.

05:22.405 --> 05:23.998
No stress.

05:28.036 --> 05:30.164
(WHISPERING) Keep it cool.

05:30.247 --> 05:32.500
No stress.

05:34.084 --> 05:35.381
(BELL DINGING)

05:40.215 --> 05:41.558
I'm sorry.

05:42.801 --> 05:45.475
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

05:58.567 --> 06:00.661
Um, hello?

06:00.735 --> 06:02.863
This is my office.
You might be in the wrong office.

06:02.946 --> 06:05.165
Hey. Hey, guys.

06:05.240 --> 06:07.208
Just take that all
down the hall and to the left.

06:07.284 --> 06:11.881
Lucky day, Dunc. New office.
Part of the new job. What?

06:11.955 --> 06:13.332
New job?

06:13.415 --> 06:15.634
Human resources.

06:15.709 --> 06:18.838
I'm an accountant. I don't know
the first thing about humans.

06:18.920 --> 06:21.764
Come on, it's just temporary.
You're far too valuable an accountant

06:21.840 --> 06:23.012
to keep in H.R. permanently.

06:23.550 --> 06:26.099
I'd love to help. I just don't know
if I'm the right man for the job.

06:26.177 --> 06:27.770
- Do you believe in this company?
- Yes.

06:27.846 --> 06:29.314
- Believe in our mission statement?
- Yes.

06:29.389 --> 06:31.391
Our employees are also our clients.
Of course.

06:31.474 --> 06:34.523
Our clients trust us because
we put our own skin in the game.

06:34.603 --> 06:36.105
- I'm in the game.
- I'm in the game, too.

06:36.187 --> 06:38.736
Your retirement account is here.
Mine is here. We're in this together.

06:38.815 --> 06:40.488
Right. Right. Right.

06:40.567 --> 06:42.615
Which is why I need you
to handle the layoffs.

06:43.904 --> 06:44.905
What?

06:44.988 --> 06:47.241
- You're a nice guy, Dunc.
- Thank you.

06:47.324 --> 06:49.076
Which is exactly what we need
right now.

06:49.159 --> 06:52.254
A nice guy, and we gotta
let some people go,

06:52.329 --> 06:54.377
and you just said
you're a team player.

06:54.456 --> 06:57.710
I am a team player,
it's just that I don't...

06:57.792 --> 07:01.046
I don't... I've never fired
anybody before in my life.

07:01.129 --> 07:03.848
It's easy, you'll love it.
I'm so glad you're on board.

07:03.924 --> 07:06.347
Um, I'll be sad to see you go.

07:06.593 --> 07:08.061
What?

07:08.136 --> 07:10.434
So. Your new office.

07:14.184 --> 07:15.401
This is a bathroom.

07:15.477 --> 07:18.196
It was a bathroom, and now
it is an office for two.

07:18.647 --> 07:19.648
Hey, there, cubie.

07:19.898 --> 07:21.946
That's what I'm saying
instead of roomie.

07:22.025 --> 07:23.368
Dunc, you know Alistair.

07:23.443 --> 07:25.662
Um... yeah.

07:25.737 --> 07:28.741
Uh, Duncan, I need you and AI
to work on a re-org chart

07:28.823 --> 07:32.828
and uh, I'm going to need to
see that first thing next week.

07:32.911 --> 07:35.460
Next week? I still have to
deal with the Darcy accounts.

07:35.538 --> 07:38.291
I have... The board of directors
asked me to make a presentation.

07:38.375 --> 07:40.798
- I have to get that done by Monday.
- You got Alistair.

07:40.877 --> 07:42.675
- You got it covered.
(SIGHS)

07:42.754 --> 07:44.256
Hey, uh, cubie.

07:44.339 --> 07:46.216
You think these toilets
are still functional?

07:46.591 --> 07:49.470
Would save us a lot of trips
down the hall.

07:51.096 --> 07:52.097
Really?

07:53.306 --> 07:54.728
Yeah.

08:00.271 --> 08:02.399
<i>SARAH: And don't forget
we have dinner with your mother</i>

08:02.482 --> 08:04.325
<i>tonight at 6 pm.</i>

08:04.401 --> 08:05.869
<i>Thank you for doing
this therapy thing.</i>

08:05.944 --> 08:08.697
<i>I think it's gonna help.
His name's Dr. Oliver Highsmith,</i>

08:08.780 --> 08:10.407
<i>and I think you're really
gonna like him.</i>

08:10.490 --> 08:12.913
<i>I know you think
all therapists are crazy,</i>

08:12.993 --> 08:15.087
<i>but I think this guy
is totally legit.</i>

08:15.161 --> 08:16.629
<i>I hope it goes well, doughnut.</i>

08:17.664 --> 08:19.462
(LAUGHING)

08:19.541 --> 08:22.590
Lactose intolerant.
Just like myself.

08:22.669 --> 08:25.764
I am not...
Did I... did I write that I was?

08:25.839 --> 08:28.683
- You checked it, yes.
- I meant no, I'm not.

08:30.010 --> 08:31.887
I don't get it, you meant no
when you say yes?

08:31.970 --> 08:34.894
I think it was just a mistake.
I am not lactose intolerant.

08:34.972 --> 08:37.020
Okay, don't make it a big issue.

08:37.933 --> 08:39.902
I'm sorry.
What's happening?

08:39.977 --> 08:41.980
Witch doctor.
Witch doctor.

08:42.063 --> 08:45.408
Shut up!!
Please, don't listen to him.

08:45.483 --> 08:48.077
He thinks he knows everything
about everybody.

08:48.153 --> 08:51.157
I can't stand him sometimes.
It's like...

08:51.239 --> 08:53.207
(GROANS, LAUGHS)

08:54.868 --> 08:57.872
All right then.
Let's get started.

09:02.751 --> 09:05.095
I want you to
come over here.

09:05.170 --> 09:07.343
Lay down. Relax.

09:07.422 --> 09:09.550
Uh, what... what far?

09:09.632 --> 09:11.179
What you came here for.

09:11.259 --> 09:13.557
Hypnosis. Not?

09:13.636 --> 09:16.105
Oh... No.

09:16.181 --> 09:18.058
I want to bypass
your conscious mind

09:18.141 --> 09:20.564
to access your subconscious mind.

09:20.643 --> 09:21.690
Ah...

09:21.770 --> 09:24.444
Where the real you might be.

09:24.522 --> 09:26.991
The true you.

09:27.484 --> 09:30.909
A light and consistent stroke

09:31.404 --> 09:35.534
over the forehead
from temple to temple

09:35.617 --> 09:38.871
relaxes the patient.

09:39.204 --> 09:40.706
Okay.

09:42.165 --> 09:46.261
No, I act... I actually don't know
if this is right for me.

09:46.336 --> 09:48.054
I mean, I'm only here
because of my wife.

09:48.129 --> 09:52.259
Uh, no offense, I'm just not...
I just don't believe in hypnosis.

09:52.342 --> 09:54.891
How about we do this,
how about we just pretend...

09:54.969 --> 09:58.223
I'll pay you, and we'll pretend
that I'm making progress.

09:58.306 --> 10:00.980
I don't need your money.

10:01.059 --> 10:04.188
- I didn't mean to offend you.
- I'm not offended.

10:04.646 --> 10:06.319
I'm just sad.

10:07.148 --> 10:08.570
Uh...

10:08.650 --> 10:11.824
I'm here on Earth
to help people.

10:12.320 --> 10:14.539
(SIGHS)
- Well, thank you for coming.

10:18.159 --> 10:21.083
Would you mind if I, uh...
if I took off?

10:21.746 --> 10:23.965
Shh.

10:25.625 --> 10:28.879
(WHISPERING) You've gotta be...
(BIRD SQUAWKS)

10:29.212 --> 10:30.555
We're done.

10:35.093 --> 10:38.393
I just want to thank you two
for being so supportive.

10:38.471 --> 10:40.565
It's kind of been a rough time.
A lot of stress at work.

10:40.640 --> 10:43.189
It has been, it's been a crazy
couple of weeks at work.

10:43.268 --> 10:45.862
Well, we love seeing you guys.

10:45.937 --> 10:47.860
And Bobby just, you know,
he loves to cook.

10:47.939 --> 10:50.362
Oh, I do, I do.

10:51.276 --> 10:53.699
Oh, Mom, don't.
Mom...

10:58.032 --> 11:00.706
(MOANING, KISSING)

11:04.664 --> 11:07.838
Oh. That is not the spiciest
dish at the table.

11:07.917 --> 11:09.885
(DUNCAN LAUGHS) Yeah.

11:09.961 --> 11:12.680
Well, thank you so much
for the food, Bobby.

11:12.755 --> 11:14.098
- Duncan?
- Yeah?

11:14.174 --> 11:16.017
You can call me Dad.
Or Daddy.

11:16.092 --> 11:17.810
- No need to.
- Papa.

11:17.886 --> 11:19.638
- Bobby is good with me.
- You know what?

11:19.721 --> 11:23.191
Don't call me Daddy.
That's reserved for somebody else.

11:23.266 --> 11:25.519
(DOORBELL RINGS)
(STOMACH GROWLS)

11:25.602 --> 11:28.731
Mmm.
That must be our special guest.

11:28.813 --> 11:31.316
- Special guest?
(WHISPERING) I don't know...

11:31.399 --> 11:34.073
Dunkie. I can't imagine
what it must be like for you.

11:34.152 --> 11:36.154
Growing up without a male
to look up to.

11:36.237 --> 11:38.331
To know what males
should act like.

11:38.406 --> 11:40.329
Every now and then
it's a little obvious.

11:40.408 --> 11:42.627
- MOM: Everybody.
- Sort of... girlie.

11:42.702 --> 11:44.670
This is Dr. Lawrence Tip,

11:44.746 --> 11:47.340
and he runs the Tip Center
for Fertility.

11:47.415 --> 11:50.885
That's right.
And we're doing really well.

11:50.960 --> 11:52.212
Duncan, I presume?

11:53.296 --> 11:54.969
Yeah. Yes.

11:55.840 --> 11:57.808
I've heard a lot about you.

11:58.384 --> 12:00.386
Are... are you two planning
on having a baby?

12:00.470 --> 12:03.269
(CHUCKLES) Oh, heavens no.
- Not the way we do it.

12:03.348 --> 12:05.146
(SIGHS)

12:06.935 --> 12:09.029
Sc Duncan,
your mother here tells me

12:09.103 --> 12:12.027
that you guys are having
a little trouble conceiving.

12:12.106 --> 12:13.858
- No. No, no, no, no, no.
- No.

12:13.942 --> 12:16.411
Sweetie, Sarah is ready.

12:16.486 --> 12:18.659
So if your little guys
are slow swimmers,

12:18.738 --> 12:20.957
maybe something can be done.

12:21.032 --> 12:23.535
Wow. Beatrice, I feel like
I may have mislead you

12:23.618 --> 12:26.292
because that is not
an issue that we're having.

12:26.371 --> 12:30.046
Duncan, if you have a problem
with erectile dysfunction,

12:30.124 --> 12:31.171
I can help you with that.

12:31.251 --> 12:33.299
Look, I just thought there
might be a problem.

12:33.378 --> 12:35.881
Your father had a problem
in that department.

12:35.964 --> 12:37.511
- I just thought...
- I don't... I don't...

12:37.590 --> 12:39.342
...need to know
about any of that.

12:39.425 --> 12:42.178
Honey, sometimes we have to
hear things we don't want to hear.

12:42.262 --> 12:44.264
It's a common affliction, Duncan.

12:44.347 --> 12:45.644
A lot of men have it.

12:45.723 --> 12:47.851
(CHUCKLES) Not me, of course.
I'm a very virile man.

12:47.934 --> 12:50.312
- Me neither. Super virile.
- Very virile.

12:50.395 --> 12:53.399
I don't know you well enough for this
to feel comfortable with me.

12:53.898 --> 12:57.072
Bobby, thank you so much
for this delicious food.

12:57.151 --> 12:58.778
If you want,
I can set up an examination.

12:58.861 --> 13:01.740
- I don't.
- Mmm, would you?

13:01.823 --> 13:03.200
- I don't.
- Great idea.

13:03.283 --> 13:06.878
In fact, maybe I can take
a look tonight while I'm here.

13:06.953 --> 13:08.455
That would be perfect!

13:08.538 --> 13:10.757
See if there's a response
to a stimulus.

13:10.832 --> 13:12.550
Are you the one
doing the stimulating?

13:12.625 --> 13:13.922
That's correct, yes.

13:14.002 --> 13:17.176
And size has nothing to do with it.
Don't be bashful.

13:17.255 --> 13:20.259
He's right. You know, I mean,
we don't have that problem.

13:20.341 --> 13:22.059
- No.
- We have the opposite problem.

13:22.135 --> 13:24.809
I mean, we have to
really take it slow.

13:24.887 --> 13:27.106
Honey, no one cares about
the size of your willie.

13:27.181 --> 13:29.604
I've seen it, it's beautiful.
It's way above average.

13:29.684 --> 13:32.153
The point is progeny.

13:32.228 --> 13:33.980
We want grandkids.

13:34.063 --> 13:37.192
In other words, there's more
than one way to choke a chicken.

13:37.275 --> 13:39.573
- Uh, wow, that's...
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

13:39.652 --> 13:41.495
That's something to think about.

13:41.571 --> 13:46.168
Oh, look at that. It's work.
I'm gonna have to take this.

13:46.784 --> 13:48.411
Yeah, hello?

13:48.494 --> 13:50.246
<i>ALISTAIR: Hey, cubie,
how's it going?</i>

13:50.330 --> 13:55.632
Two things. First of all,
the toilets do nut work properly.

13:56.169 --> 13:57.091
Uh-huh.

13:57.170 --> 13:58.171
<i>Second point.</i>

13:58.254 --> 14:00.803
I've looked into the Murphy
report on your computer...

14:00.882 --> 14:02.634
You're using my computer?

14:02.717 --> 14:04.970
Yes, and the good news is,
I found it.

14:05.053 --> 14:06.054
<i>The bad news is,</i>

14:06.137 --> 14:09.607
<i>I think I may have deleted
something important.</i>

14:09.682 --> 14:10.934
- You what?
(STOMACH GROWLS)

14:11.017 --> 14:13.111
<i>Yeah, it was a folder called</i>

14:13.186 --> 14:15.780
"Board of directors presentation."

14:15.855 --> 14:17.448
<i>What?
Are you fucking kidding me?</i>

14:17.523 --> 14:19.742
<i>I've been working on that
for a year.</i>

14:20.443 --> 14:23.572
Oh, my God.
This is bad.

14:23.654 --> 14:27.329
Honestly, I was flustered
by the toilet situation.

14:27.408 --> 14:29.502
I called the janitor.
That's going to be better.

14:29.577 --> 14:31.796
- That will...
- Whatever, whatever.

14:31.871 --> 14:34.590
Whatever. I'll come in tonight.
I'll take care of it.

14:34.665 --> 14:36.292
Bye.

14:36.376 --> 14:38.879
(STOMACH GROWLING)
(GROANING)

14:39.462 --> 14:41.135
Fuck, fuck, fuck.

14:44.675 --> 14:45.972
(KEYS RATTLING)

14:56.145 --> 14:57.988
- Oh, God.
(FARTING)

15:00.358 --> 15:02.281
(BATHROOM SOUNDS)

15:03.736 --> 15:05.864
(BATHROOM SOUNDS CONTINUE)

15:05.947 --> 15:07.290
(DUNCAN GROANING)

15:11.744 --> 15:13.337
(GROANS)

15:15.748 --> 15:19.719
Did you know that the leading
cause of divorce is children?

15:19.794 --> 15:21.216
That's not true.

15:21.295 --> 15:24.174
That is just what children
believe in their hearts.

15:24.257 --> 15:26.430
Kids are a huge responsibility.

15:26.509 --> 15:28.887
It's just a stressful
thing, honey.

15:28.970 --> 15:30.597
I don't know if I could
do it right now.

15:30.680 --> 15:33.354
Okay, look, I didn't say that
I wanted to have a kid today.

15:33.433 --> 15:35.185
I don't need to have
a kid tomorrow.

15:35.268 --> 15:37.316
Okay, good because
tomorrow I have plans.

15:37.395 --> 15:39.773
I gotta go see the doctor.
I gotta get the car washed.

15:39.856 --> 15:41.858
Honestly, so if you're planning
on popping out a kid,

15:41.941 --> 15:44.285
I just don't think it's
an appropriate day to do it.

15:44.360 --> 15:45.987
(CHUCKLES)

15:46.404 --> 15:48.577
I'm just saying that...

15:48.906 --> 15:50.158
...I want to have a family,

15:50.241 --> 15:52.243
and I want to have a family
with you.

15:52.326 --> 15:55.250
I know. I want to have
a baby, too.

15:55.329 --> 15:58.333
I just...
(SIGHS)

16:00.209 --> 16:03.554
Phil put me in charge of layoffs.
Today.

16:05.882 --> 16:07.976
Why did you agree to that?

16:08.050 --> 16:09.472
(CHUCKLES)
What am I gonna say?

16:09.552 --> 16:12.101
All you have to really do
is just say no.

16:12.180 --> 16:14.274
(CHUCKLES) It's just...

16:14.348 --> 16:17.522
It's not a great time
to make big changes right now.

16:17.602 --> 16:20.776
Can we just let things
settle down a little bit?

16:20.855 --> 16:22.653
- Okay.
- Yeah?

16:22.732 --> 16:24.609
- All right.
- I'm sorry.

16:27.278 --> 16:28.530
(STOMACH GROWLING)

16:28.613 --> 16:30.536
What is going on down there?

16:31.073 --> 16:33.997
Awful things.
